---
// Reproduction for https://github.com/withastro/astro/issues/16524.
// The bug appears when a scoped style nests `:where(& > ...)` under a class
// selector. With `vite.css.transformer: 'lightningcss'`, lightningcss flattens
// the nesting BEFORE the Astro compiler injects the scope attribute, which
// (without the fix) causes `[data-astro-cid-...]` to bind to the matched
// child instead of the parent.
---
<html>
	<head>
		<title>lightningcss-scoped-nesting</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="parent">
			<span>a</span>
			<span>b</span>
			<span>c</span>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.parent {
		display: flex;
		:where(& > :not(:last-child)) {
			margin-inline-end: 24px;
		}
	}
</style>
